com.ibm.team.build.client.iterator

Interface IBuildResultRecordIterator


  • public interface IBuildResultRecordIterator
    Provides the ability to iterate through the build result records associated with a set of build results.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int MAX_BUILD_RESULT_RECORDS
      The maximum number of build result records that can be retrieved in one invocation of next(int, IProgressMonitor).

      • next

        com.ibm.team.build.internal.common.model.dto.IBuildResultRecord[] next(int numRecords,
                                                                       org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                                                                throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                                                       java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the next numRecords of build result records and positions the iterator at the next record beyond them. Less than the desired number of records may be returned if there are not enough records left to fulfill the request.
        Parameters:
        numRecords - The number of build result records to retrieve.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The next numRecords of build result records
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the specified numRecords exceed MAX_BUILD_RESULT_RECORDS.
